ness there could point to sacroiliitis.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042035,0.088181,0.10001,0.10478,0.10098,0.098101,0.094444,0.086229,0.090363,0.075615,0.063402,0.055869],"unified_progress":[0.043893,0.075782,0.094492,0.10552,0.10928,0.10571,0.10039,0.091609,0.093084,0.073873,0.058407,0.047956]},{"section":8,"text":"The limited forward flexion of the lumbar spine on exam makes me think of spinal involvement.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053468,0.10082,0.10018,0.098048,0.094359,0.09457,0.090195,0.086417,0.085533,0.074029,0.064357,0.05803],"unified_progress":[0.054433,0.086574,0.094501,0.10126,0.10331,0.099311,0.09591,0.091134,0.087828,0.07377,0.060941,0.051027]},{"section":9,"text":"The eye symptoms\u2014discomfort and photophobia\u2014are concerning.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.064026,0.1129,0.10216,0.090962,0.087421,0.090636,0.086105,0.087837,0.079593,0.073825,0.066806,0.057729],"unified_progress":[0.065645,0.096667,0.092609,0.092325,0.092191,0.093053,0.089719,0.091301,0.085139,0.078904,0.068365,0.054082]},{"section":10,"text":"An inflamed eye with a constricted pupil might be uveitis, specifically anterior uveitis.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043229,0.085435,0.093495,0.09739,0.098276,0.098252,0.09664,0.090982,0.087257,0.078982,0.068868,0.061193],"unified_progress":[0.043435,0.07267,0.090538,0.095187,0.099371,0.10345,0.098623,0.09442,0.09261,0.082107,0.070405,0.057187]},{"section":11,"text":"I remember that ankylosing spondylitis often has associated uveitis as an extra-articular manifestation.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032817,0.067914,0.082159,0.094618,0.10203,0.1032,0.10347,0.096182,0.08759,0.089358,0.072906,0.067753],"unified_progress":[0.036825,0.058997,0.07958,0.090671,0.095893,0.10909,0.103,0.10044,0.095058,0.090598,0.076679,0.063178]},{"section":12,"text":"The x-rays showing sacroiliitis are a big clue.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036669,0.078271,0.091869,0.097277,0.096199,0.09565,0.09503,0.089987,0.092319,0.083063,0.074994,0.068674],"unified_progress":[0.037877,0.070051,0.086588,0.097784,0.10288,0.10096,0.09867,0.094744,0.094375,0.083094,0.072523,0.060448]},{"section":13,"text":"Sacroiliitis is a key feature in the diagnosis of spondyloarthritis.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031897,0.06792,0.083219,0.094558,0.10015,0.10039,0.10072,0.094276,0.088491,0.088543,0.075716,0.074114],"unified_progress":[0.035399,0.059694,0.077986,0.090541,0.095571,0.11033,0.10158,0.098543,0.094352,0.089763,0.078177,0.068063]},{"section":14,"text":"Ankylosing spondylitis is a type of spondyloarthritis that primarily affects the axial skeleton.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029043,0.062316,0.076785,0.090605,0.10033,0.10376,0.10518,0.098464,0.090738,0.093736,0.076364,0.072674],"unified_progress":[0.037971,0.056015,0.075117,0.088105,0.094733,0.10657,0.10346,0.10205,0.097134,0.092019,0.078773,0.068048]},{"section":15,"text":"The patient's age is also relevant because ankylosing spondylitis typically presents in young adults, often in their 20s.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036245,0.070127,0.078729,0.086539,0.093666,0.1002,0.099267,0.097525,0.092165,0.092486,0.080875,0.07217],"unified_progress":[0.064336,0.083883,0.083289,0.085018,0.088119,0.092964,0.090721,0.094466,0.089035,0.085782,0.076421,0.065966]},{"section":16,"text":"Other possibilities to consider might be reactive arthritis, but that usually follows an infection and might have more involvement of the lower extremities or other joints.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023,0.055654,0.071211,0.083024,0.091851,0.098179,0.10577,0.10557,0.10312,0.10145,0.092477,0.068699],"unified_progress":[0.030538,0.058121,0.075752,0.083775,0.09489,0.099059,0.10176,0.10488,0.10359,0.10652,0.085027,0.056082]},{"section":17,"text":"Inflammatory bowel disease-associated spondylitis could be another thought, but there's no mention of gastrointestinal symptoms here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02182,0.053788,0.06892,0.080155,0.088921,0.096613,0.10437,0.10723,0.10596,0.1049,0.095791,0.071521],"unified_progress":[0.031766,0.061075,0.074081,0.082206,0.0918,0.09662,0.10053,0.10578,0.10455,0.10829,0.08713,0.056177]},{"section":18,"text":"The combination of sacroiliitis on x-ray, inflammatory back pain, and uveitis really points towards ankylosing spondylitis.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027081,0.059917,0.073875,0.082932,0.088466,0.092216,0.096058,0.095723,0.098656,0.09864,0.094355,0.092081],"unified_progress":[0.032357,0.056196,0.071116,0.082464,0.089663,0.096773,0.099104,0.098979,0.10076,0.098092,0.092811,0.081679]},{"section":19,"text":"HLA-B27 is commonly associated with this condition, though the case doesn't mention genetic testing.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032703,0.067837,0.081046,0.08798,0.091961,0.09461,0.096443,0.09566,0.093447,0.092807,0.08593,0.079576],"unified_progress":[0.04621,0.075189,0.08253,0.086817,0.091643,0.09325,0.094511,0.093961,0.091222,0.088906,0.082997,0.072764]},{"section":20,"text":"But given the clinical picture, that's the most likely diagnosis.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033126,0.064626,0.077415,0.083522,0.085406,0.085483,0.088784,0.089592,0.090597,0.094902,0.093279,0.11327],"unified_progress":[0.038905,0.054882,0.063794,0.074141,0.078293,0.082335,0.086256,0.091157,0.094189,0.10182,0.11046,0.12376]}]}}